text: Norman Surplus (1963 - 18 April 2022) was a Northern Irish pilot. He traveled around the world in an autogyro, nicknamed "Roxy". His trip began in 2010 and ended on 28 June 2019. Surplus died on 18 April 2022. ==References== Category:1963 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Northern Ireland people Category:Aviators
